            "has-agent",
            "is-show-hn"
          ],
          "value_score": 4,
          "storyText": "Creator of browser-use library here. At Browser Use we spend a lot of time thinking about the bitter lesson of agentic frameworks. A few days we did an experiment that combines replacing Playwright with CDP and giving the LLM complete freedom (building with autoresearch from ground up) to do whatever it knows from pretraining. I think this is the simplest way to give an AI control of a real browser: raw CDP, and let the agent write its own tools. ~600 lines total. Example: I forgot to implement ",
